<body>
  <div>
    <h1>üîê Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: January 2026</p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and
      protected when you access or use the website
      shelters-production.up.railway.app. This website is a student project
      created for learning and demonstration purposes only.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>
      We collect limited information when users create an account or interact
      with the website. This may include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Username</li>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Password (stored securely using database encryption techniques)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Providing an email address is not mandatory for meaningful use of the
      project. Users may enter any email address, and email verification is not
      enforced.
    </p>
    <p>
      We may also collect basic technical data such as browser type and session
      identifiers for functionality purposes.
    </p>

    <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <p>The collected information is used only to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create and manage user accounts</li>
      <li>Allow users to create, edit, and delete lists</li>
      <li>Allow users to add, edit, and delete reviews</li>
      <li>Maintain login sessions</li>
      <li>Improve the overall functionality of the project</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data is not used for marketing, not sold, and not shared for
      commercial purposes.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>3. Cookies and Session Storage</h4>
    <p>
      This website uses cookies strictly for session management and
      authentication purposes. Cookies are used to keep users logged in and to
      ensure secure access to features. No tracking, advertising, or analytics
      cookies are used.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>4. Third-Party Services</h4>
    <p>
      This project relies on the following third-party services to function:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>MongoDB Atlas for database storage</li>
      <li>Cloudinary for image storage</li>
      <li>Railway for hosting</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These services may process data as required for their technical operation,
      in accordance with their own privacy policies.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>5. Data Security</h4>
    <p>
      Reasonable security measures are implemented to protect stored
      information. However, since this is a student project, no system can be
      guaranteed to be completely secure. Users should not submit sensitive or
      personal information.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>6. Data Visibility</h4>
    <p>
      User email addresses are not publicly displayed on the website. Only
      usernames and user-generated content (such as lists or reviews) may be
      visible to other visitors.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>7. Account Availability</h4>
    <p>
      Account creation is temporarily enabled for demonstration purposes and may
      be disabled at any time. Once disabled, users will no longer be able to
      create accounts, submit reviews, or perform write actions.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>8. Changes to This Policy</h4>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time without prior notice.
      Changes will be reflected on this page.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>9. Contact</h4>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the
      project owner through the website repository or platform where this
      project is shared.
    </p>
